wendy graff the clayman institute for gender research skip to main content standford university the clayman institute for gender research the clayman institute for gender research home programs news strategic focus events about research fellowships library media center gender news no news found events february 29 2012 7 00pm women's torah female scribes artists and visionaries you are here home people wendy graff wendy graff women's torah project leader wendy graff is head of the women's torah project which has created the first known torah to be collaboratively written by women from around the world graff began the project when she realized that even though her daughter could proudly carry and read from the torah she would not be allowed to transcribe it once graff realized that she could help change that for present and future generations she couldn t go back wendy graff is a community member of kadima forward in hebrew which is seattle's oldest progressive jewish organization donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
